- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and their complexity measures.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial and algebraic structures related to regular languages.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of various operations on regular languages, which is a topic of interest in information theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of regular languages under various measures.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still relevant as the paper involves the study of regular languages and their properties, which can be seen as a topic in mathematical logic.
